claim.claim-text:
Apparatus (10) for removing emboli from a vessel during an interventional procedure, the apparatus (10) comprising:
a catheter (20) having
a proximal end (21), a distal end (22) and a lumen (23),
the proximal end (21) in fluid communication with the distal end (22) via the lumen (23),
the distal end (22) configured for intravascular placement in the vessel;
an actuator (26) coupled to the catheter (20) via an inflow path (28) and an outflow path (29);
a flexible liner (36) disposed within the lumen (23) of the catheter (20),
the liner (36) selectively movable in response to the actuator (26) between a first position collapsed against an interior surface of the catheter (20) and a second position wherein the liner (36) expands into the lumen (23) thus providing an outflow lumen defined by the flexible liner (36) and the interior surface of catheter (20);
a filter (31) disposed in the outflow path (29);
the actuator (26) adapted to
aspirate blood from the vessel through the catheter lumen (23) and the inflow path (28) during a first mode of operation thus collapsing the selectively movable liner (36) into the first position and to
re-perfuse blood filtered by the filter (31) into the vessel during a second mode of operation, the blood exiting the filter (31) and the outflow path (29) thus expanding the flexible liner (36) into the second position, the blood flowing through the outflow lumen into the patient's vessel.
